==============================================================
COMPONENT 4 — ANDROID APK (Capacitor WebView wrapper)
==============================================================

--- APPROACH ---
Use Capacitor.js to wrap the Electron app's React frontend as a WebView app.
The Android app loads the same React UI, but calls your backend API directly.
The license key is stored in Capacitor's Preferences (secure storage).

--- SETUP ---
1. Take the /renderer React app from the Electron project
2. Run: npx cap init + npx cap add android
3. Build React app → copy to /public → sync with Capacitor
4. Override API base URL for mobile: use VITE_API_URL env var
5. Build APK: ./gradlew assembleRelease
6. Host the APK on your website dashboard for download

--- ANDROID SPECIFIC ADJUSTMENTS ---
- Add internet permission to AndroidManifest.xml
- Set allowMixedContent false, usesCleartextTraffic false
- Handle back button to go back in WebView history
- Set WebView settings: setJavaScriptEnabled(true), setDomStorageEnabled(true)
- Disable zoom controls for app-like feel
- Set app icon and splash screen

